  rsync -auz -e ssh remote:/dir/ . &amp;&amp; rsync -auz -e ssh . remote:/dir/

You can always use the --dry-run option for testing.

Check out --modify-window option when syncing with a non-POSIX file system like FAT.</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
